Including Plots

You can also embed plots, for example:

myPalette <- colorRampPalette(rev(brewer.pal(11, "Spectral")))
results_by_lrne <- ddply(results, .(n_epoch,learning_rate, block), summarize, med_validation_error=median(validation_error))
ggplot(filter(results_by_lrne, block=="results1"), aes(y=n_epoch, x=learning_rate, fill=med_validation_error)) + geom_tile() + scale_fill_gradientn(colours=myPalette(100), limits=c(0.68,0.78))

ggplot(filter(results_by_lrne, block=="results3"), aes(y=n_epoch, x=learning_rate, fill=med_validation_error)) + geom_tile() + scale_fill_gradientn(colours=myPalette(100), limits=c(0.68,0.78))

myPalette <- colorRampPalette(rev(brewer.pal(11, "Spectral")))

ggplot(filter(results_by_nebs, block=="results1"), aes(y=n_epoch, x=batch_size, fill=med_validation_error)) + geom_tile() + scale_fill_gradientn(colours=myPalette(100), limits=c(0.68,0.78))

ggplot(filter(results_by_nebs, block=="results3"), aes(y=n_epoch, x=batch_size, fill=med_validation_error)) + geom_tile() + scale_fill_gradientn(colours=myPalette(100), limits=c(0.68,0.78))
